main event: A single orange object was observed for 20 seconds at 45 degrees elevation, moving at 38 degrees per minute in a northwest direction.
interesting points: The object was observed at coordinates 32.02N 174.15W in the Pacific Ocean.
The sighting was reported via a CIRVIS (Communications Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report.
The report was transmitted to the CIA per Form 1392 #46.
The conclusion was that there was 'Insufficient data for evaluation' and the direction of the object was 'wrong for satellite'.
The report notes that objects at 45 degrees elevation for 20 seconds are 'not weather balloons'.
